Two persons were injured when fire gutted a storey building behind Tejuosho Market in Yaba, Lagos on Thursday, reports the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). The Director General of LASEMA, Dr Olufemi Oke-Osanyintolu, said that the fire, caused by power surge, was put out by rescue officials and Lagos State Fire Service. He said that the Tejuosho fire started from one of the rooms before escalating to other parts of the building. Oke-Osanyintolu said that the intensity of the fire had caused physical cracks of the building. He, however, said that no loss of life but two male adult sustained injuries. Vanguard News Nigeria. According to Director-General of Lagos State Emergency Management Agency, LASEMA, Dr. Femi Oke-Osantintolu, who confirmed the incident, the intensity of the fire led to physical cracks which eventually led to collapse of the building. November 14, 2019 In "News" By Olasunkanmi Akoni Tragedy struck in Lagos again, Friday, November 1st, when a two storey building, still under construction, suddenly collapsed at Glover Court, Ikoyi, Lagos. At press time, four out of the five trapped construction workers in the collapsed building were rescued, while the remaining worker was yet to… November 2, 2019 In "News" By Olasunkanmi Akoni Tragedy struck in Lagos again, Friday, November 1st, when a two-storey building, still under construction, suddenly collapsed at Glover Court, Ikoyi, Lagos.  At press time, four out of the five trapped construction workers in the collapsed building were rescued, while the remaining worker was yet to be… November 1, 2019 In "News"